setwd("//ama-mobility4/ITSdata/DAS-Rural Safety/FHWA Rural Safety (Subasish Das)/Task 4/Function_class_level_with_crash/OH/csv_files")

df_PAI <- fread('OH_Principal_Arterial_Rural_Interstate_1_TMC_TT_SI_reduce_withCrash.csv', showProgress = FALSE)
dim(df_PAI)
## [1] 12193920       30
### Calculating Speed
df_PAI$Spd_All = 3600*df_PAI$DISTANCE/df_PAI$Travel_TIME_ALL_VEHICLES
df_PAI$Spd_Car = 3600*df_PAI$DISTANCE/df_PAI$Travel_TIME_PASSENGER_VEHICLES
df_PAI$Spd_Truck = 3600*df_PAI$DISTANCE/df_PAI$Travel_TIME_FREIGHT_TRUCKS


### Month, Day
df_PAI$date <- as.character(df_PAI$DATE)
df_PAI$date <- str_pad(df_PAI$DATE, 8, pad = "0")
df_PAI$Month <- substr(df_PAI$date, start = 1, stop = 2)
df_PAI$Day   <- substr(df_PAI$date, start = 3, stop = 4)
df_PAI$Year  <- substr(df_PAI$date, start = 5, stop = 8)
df_PAI$MonthDay <- paste0(df_PAI$Month,"_", df_PAI$Day)
head(df_PAI)
day1<- df_PAI[,-c(1)] %>% group_by(MonthDay) %>% summarize(Speed_All_Mean=mean(Spd_All, na.rm=TRUE))
day1
# Step 2: Examine Data
speed_clean <- tsclean(ts(day1$Speed_All_Mean))
plot.ts(speed_clean)

# ggplot() + geom_line(data = Q1, aes(x = TimeStamp, y = speed_clean)) + ylab('Cleaned Speed Records')

day1$cnt_ma = ma(speed_clean, order=7) # using the clean count with no outliers
day1$cnt_ma30 = ma(speed_clean, order=30)
# Step 3: Decompose Your Data
count_ma = ts(na.omit(speed_clean), frequency=30)
decomp = stl(count_ma, s.window="periodic")
deseasonal_cnt <- seasadj(decomp)
plot(decomp)

# Step 4: Stationarity
# statinary test for original data
adf.test(count_ma, alternative = "stationary")
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  count_ma
## Dickey-Fuller = -3.4967, Lag order = 7, p-value = 0.04315
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
# statinary test for deseasonal data
adf.test(deseasonal_cnt, alternative = "stationary")
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  deseasonal_cnt
## Dickey-Fuller = -3.4858, Lag order = 7, p-value = 0.0442
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
# statinary test for difference data
d1 = diff(deseasonal_cnt)
adf.test(d1, alternative = "stationary")
## Warning in adf.test(d1, alternative = "stationary"): p-value smaller than
## printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  d1
## Dickey-Fuller = -9.9838, Lag order = 7, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
# Step 5: Autocorrelations and Choosing Model Order
# check ACF and PACF
acf2(count_ma)

# AR(1)? AR(2)? 
acf2(deseasonal_cnt)

# Step 6: Fitting an ARIMA model
# fit deseasonal data
auto.arima(deseasonal_cnt, seasonal=FALSE)
## Series: deseasonal_cnt 
## ARIMA(4,1,4) 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ar1      ar2     ar3      ar4      ma1     ma2      ma3     ma4
##       0.6089  -1.1206  0.7582  -0.4971  -0.9659  0.9014  -1.0832  0.3436
## s.e.  0.1022   0.0836  0.0841   0.0600   0.1117  0.1295   0.0935  0.0936
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 0.3059:  log likelihood=-297.97
## AIC=613.93   AICc=614.44   BIC=649.01
# fit seasonal data
auto.arima(deseasonal_cnt, seasonal=TRUE)
## Series: deseasonal_cnt 
## ARIMA(2,1,2)(2,0,0)[30] with drift 
## 
## Coefficients:
##          ar1      ar2      ma1     ma2     sar1     sar2   drift
##       1.2186  -0.9326  -1.3803  0.9361  -0.0652  -0.0594  0.0014
## s.e.  0.0222   0.0224   0.0222  0.0242   0.0628   0.0769  0.0206
## 
## sigma^2 estimated as 0.3183:  log likelihood=-306.09
## AIC=628.17   AICc=628.58   BIC=659.35
# Step 7: Evaluate and Iterate
# (try different model)
# fit deseasonal data
fit<-auto.arima(deseasonal_cnt, seasonal=FALSE)
tsdisplay(residuals(fit), lag.max=45, main='(4,1,2) Model Residuals')

# step 8 forcast
fcast <- forecast(fit, h=30)
plot(fcast)

# fit seasonal data
fit_s<-auto.arima(deseasonal_cnt, seasonal=TRUE)
tsdisplay(residuals(fit_s), lag.max=45, main='(4,1,3) Model Residuals')

# step 8 forcast
fcast <- forecast(fit_s, h=30)
plot(fcast)
